Olufemi Olaniyi, Ibadan The Chief of Defence Staff, Gen. Leo Irhabor, has led other military chiefs to hold a meeting with the Oyo State Governor, Mr. Seyi Makinde. The military chiefs were said to have first visited the 2 Division first and they are said to be on their way to the Governor’s Office at the Secretariat in Agodi to meet with the governor. The Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Mr Taiwo Adisa, confirmed this to our correspondent. He said, ” Yes, they are in Ibadan already. They are almost here to meet the governor.” There have been security issues in Oyo State and how to tackle the problem is expected to be one of the issues to be discussed at the meeting.